title: Join me at Reid’s Palace on Madeira Island #SundaySupper
summary: You can never have too many main course recipes, so give Join me at Reid’s Palace on Madeiran Island #SundaySupper a try. One portion of this dish contains around 64g of protein, 31g of fat, and a total of 740 calories. This recipe serves 9 and costs $5.09 per serving. 100 people were glad they tried this recipe. If you have wine, prawns headless 8/12, parsley, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the lemon juice you could follow this main course with the Lemon Shortbread Cookies with Lemon Icing {A Tribute to Aunt Roxanne} as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 90%. This score is great. Try Ice Palace, My Commander’s Palace Salad, and Lake Palace Hotel's Aubergine for similar recipes.
